In older versions of {{package|sys-apps/portage}}
<noinclude>'''{{Path|/usr/portage}}''' was [[Article description::the default <var>location</var> value in the {{Path|/usr/share/portage/config/repos.conf}} file for the [https://gitweb.gentoo.org/repo/gentoo.git/tree/ main ebuild repository] on Gentoo-based systems.]]  It has been [https://gitweb.gentoo.org/proj/portage.git/commit/cnf/repos.conf?id{{=}}ef8469befbd7b61f1bae8f21ffd95e0c0306a4f8 replaced] with '''{{path|/var/db/repos/gentoo}}'''.  Alternative <var>location</var> values can be detected by running the {{c|portageq}} utility:

{{Cmd|portageq get_repo_path / gentoo|output=<pre>
/usr/portage</pre>}}

For more information see [[:/etc/portage/repos.conf/gentoo.conf]].

